      <div class="rbp-nbn-head">
        <div class="rbp-nbn-eye">Answers</div>
        <h2 class="rbp-nbn-h2">Business NBN questions</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="rbp-nbn-faq" role="list">
        <details open>
          <summary>What is Business NBN?</summary>
          <div class="rbp-nbn-faq-body">Business NBN is a broadband internet service delivered over the National Broadband Network (NBN) infrastructure. It is designed for business premises and typically includes higher upload speeds, static IP options, and priority support pathways compared to residential plans.</div>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>How do I know which NBN technology is at my address?</summary>
          <div class="rbp-nbn-faq-body">Use the address availability checker above to find out. Your result will indicate the connection technology (FTTP, HFC, FTTN, FTTC) available at your premises, which determines the speed tiers you can access.</div>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>What are typical evening speeds?</summary>
          <div class="rbp-nbn-faq-body">Typical evening download speeds refer to the speeds most customers will experience between 7pm and 11pm on weekday evenings — the busiest time on the network. Actual speeds may vary based on connection technology, hardware, and network conditions.</div>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>Do I need to be an RBP member to access Business NBN?</summary>
          <div class="rbp-nbn-faq-body">No. Business NBN is available to all business customers. However, RBP members receive structured support pathways and assistance with the connection process as part of their membership inclusions.</div>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>How long does the connection process take?</summary>
          <div class="rbp-nbn-faq-body">The timeframe varies by address and connection type. After availability is confirmed, connection typically takes between 1–4 weeks depending on whether a technician installation visit is required. Your RBP support team will confirm expected timeframes.</div>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>Can I keep my existing phone number?</summary>
          <div class="rbp-nbn-faq-body">In most cases, yes. Number portability is available for most existing business numbers. Confirm this during the application process with the RBP team.</div>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>What happens if my NBN has an outage?</summary>
          <div class="rbp-nbn-faq-body">Business NBN plans include support pathways for fault reporting and resolution. Priority support is available on Business and Enterprise plan tiers (subject to final plan confirmation). Use the Help Center or contact support directly for outage assistance.</div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

